# Project Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ with App Router (src/app/ directory)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS for all styling
- Zustand for client-side state management
- Supabase for database and storage
- Resend for email
- @react-pdf/renderer for PDF generation
- Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) for AI narrative generation

## Code Style
- Use functional components with hooks
- Use TypeScript interfaces, not types, for object shapes
- Use named exports, not default exports (except for page components)
- Keep components under 200 lines. Extract into smaller components if longer.
- All API routes go in src/app/api/
- All reusable components go in src/components/
- All data/constants go in src/lib/
- Store types in src/types/

## Design
- Color palette: Dark Blue #1B3A5C, Teal #1A8A7D, White #FFFFFF, Light Gray #F4F7FA
- Font: Inter (import from Google Fonts)
- Never use em dashes anywhere. Use commas, periods, colons, or separate sentences.
- Mobile-responsive design required on all pages

## Architecture
- Assessment form state lives in a Zustand store (src/lib/store.ts)
- Scoring logic is pure functions in src/lib/scoring.ts
- PDF generation happens server-side in API routes
- AI narrative generation happens server-side in /api/generate-narrative
